what_worked: Applied early_filter, pushdown, materialize_cte: Created `filtered_item` CTE to pre-filter items by category, split the original `all_sales` CTE into separate `sales_1999` and `sales_1998` CTEs with year filters pushed into each UNION branch, changed UNION to UNION ALL for better performance, and used explicit JOIN syntax throughout.
why_it_worked: Applying selective filters early reduces intermediate row counts before expensive operations; Pushing predicates closer to table scans reduces data volume in upper operators; Materializing a CTE used multiple times prevents redundant re-computation
